						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Jalanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman (Āditya I) Year 24: 895 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Pridipadiyār (Prithivīpati), son of Māramaraiyar (ie Mārasiṁha) gifted a silver kettle with a spout weighing three hundred and seventeen <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> to god of Māhādēvar at Tiruvūṟal, on the occasion of the solar eclipse in the month of <hi rend="italic">Āṇi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi> Vol. XIX. pp. 87-88.</p>						

						<p>Also in S.I.I. Vol. V 1368.</p>						

						</summary>
